[Student "S"]
{SOUTH has a perfect hand on which to use Fourth Suit Forcing. If North can stop 
\Ss, then 3NT would be a great contract.

There is one problem - if SOUTH bids 1\S at her second turn it is NOT considered 
FSF, so she must jump to 2\S.

NORTH, win a fine \S stopper, bids 3NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "E:Q75.JT76.A8.KQJ3 A96.A542.964.842 K8432.KQ83.73.A5 JT.9.KQJT52.T976"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
